Lasgalen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/21/01 11:01:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Camp Courtesy</span><hr size=1> Months ago, I was KSed on the Dylin camp. By KSed, I mean that I was there for hours before the other person arrived, engaged Dylin before the other person engaged him, but the KSer still nuked Dylin silly/looted page/immediately camped out. Of course a petition did exactly nothing. This upset me greatly, but I got my page later anyway.<br>
<br>
I bring this up to point out that I am sympathetic to those who are having problems getting their ToV. It's a pain in the butt on a TLC/anti-NoDrop server, and that's a fact.<br>
<br>
However, here's another couple facts we should all keep in mind. Just because a person in a guild gets a page, it doesn't mean that another person in that guild can't get the next page. If the Order of the Oaken wants to position a member at Dylin's spawn 24/7 for the next two weeks...that's their prerogotive. Would it be rude if they did that? Yes, I think so but not illegal or dishonorable.<br>
<br>
Also, if a class that wouldn't use the ToV wants to camp it for a friend or for sale, that's their right. If a warrior shows up, no one is there, and he waits for and kills Dylin...hurray for him. He has a nice piece of gear for his trouble to trade for something else. Is it a little rude, considerring how important that item is for many clerics, shaman and druids? Yes, I think so, but it is not illegal or dishonorable.<br>
<br>
Let's face it folks, there are two points here that are valid. If someone has already engaged Dylin and someone else intervenes and steals it...that is actively against the PnP. If someone is there ahead of you waiting for Dylin to spawn, and you jump Dylin while they are buffing/harmonizing/waiting for bandits to walk out of range....that is &quot;legal&quot; but rude as hell.<br>
<br>
However, anything beyond that is just plain setting yourself up for a fall. If a guildmate kills Dylin...of course they are going to tell their guildmembers when he died and when he'll be back. That's what guilds are for. I'm sure the Order of the Oaken has many druids and clerics that want the ToV and don't have it. If a few people in their guild try to get it for them, then they are being nice, helpful, normal guildmates.<br>
<br>
I have not interracted with the Order of the Oaken. I don't know anything about this particular situation. But, if any guild decides to organize a 24 hour per day Dylin-a-thon for a few days in a row, to outfit their members with ToV...that is their right and it is wrong for people to call them a bunch of dishonorable, farming, jerks. The members of a guild have just as much right to be there as anyone else.<br>
<br>
If they monopolize the spawn for several days, and we start seeing them selling ToV's, then that becomes just plain rude. But I haven't seen anyone claiming that yet.<br>
<br>
I sympathize with the plight of the orginal poster, but I think it's unfair based on the information in this thread to start flaming an entire guild based on a few days activity. Tempers are starting to grow out of proportion to the actual events here. I would hope we could all get along a bit better than that.<br>
<br>
 <p>Grimwyrd Storm<BR>
(Lux Aeternam)<BR>
28th Human Druid of Karana<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/21/01 11:13:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   From the Play Nice Policies</span><hr size=1> From the Play Nice Policies:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Contested Spawns<br>
There are cases where two or more groups wish to kill the same thing.  In these cases, the groups are required to compromise.  If an equitable compromise cannot be reached between players prior to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  EverQuest</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Customer Service Staff involvement, the EQCSR will mandate a binding compromise.  Refusing to abide by a compromise mandated by an EQCSR will be considered disruption.  It is therefore strongly suggested that groups make every attempt to reach a compromise that they can live with prior to involving an EQCSR, who may mandate a compromise that does not suit you to the extent that a player-devised compromise would.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Note: A &quot;group&quot; in this case is defined as a party of one or more characters that are united in a common belief or goal and are capable of completing that goal.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Until Krystallgold intervened, none of the other members of this guild were willing to compromise.  Instead, they cast Harmony on me, called me a &quot;Kill-stealer&quot;, and told me I had to wait until they got yet another page before I got in line.<br>
