Lasgalen <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A> at: 12/21/01 11:16:24 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/22/01 3:03:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: From the Play Nice Policies</span><hr size=1> I shouldn't have even posted in this thread, cause it's no business of mine, but I did so I'll say one more thing.<br>
<br>
One problem with this camp is that (for most classes) if you are young enough to kill Dylin and not be affected by TLC, then you are young enough to get your butt handed to you by all the smugglers.<br>
<br>
So, let's look at it this hypothetical way. You've been there for quite some time waiting for Dylin to spawn. He finally spawns, but you know you can't kill him without getting killed by smugglers, so you notify you're druid guildmate that Dylin is there and ask him/her to gate to highpass and Harmony the smugglers. Maybe that seemed reasonable to you, because then both of you don't have to sit there for hours.<br>
<br>
Right before your druid guildmate friend arrives, someone logs in, sees that Dylin up, and kills him. Would you be upset? Now be honest Lasgalen, would you be upset under those circumstances? Would you consider it &quot;cutting in line&quot;?<br>
<br>
Sure, that person wouldn't technically be KSing, since you hadn't attacked yet, but would you still consider them rude if you had been there waiting for Dylin for hours and someone else popped him while you awaited your reinforcements? This is an ugly camp thanks to a combination of TLC and the proximity of high level smugglers.<br>
<br>
Technically, the monk and druid had no right to call you a KSer, because they hadn't gotten their attack organized before you jumped Dylin. They should have both been there waiting for hours if they wanted to make sure they had the manpower to kill Dylin in spite of the smugglers. But I can understand if they were disappointed and frustrated with your actions. And I think it was very nice of you to give them the page.<br>
<br>
But after that, I disagree with you. There is no &quot;being in line&quot; for this spawn and &quot;taking turns&quot; if YOU don't stay there. If you left and popped back in 6 hours later saying &quot;my turn, my turn&quot; to the people that had been sitting there for hours, then I'm not surprised you met with very little cooperation.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, the only &quot;fair&quot; way for such a contested spawn to be dealt with is for whoever is physically there first, should have first shot at Dylin when he spawns. If there are people already there and you want a &quot;turn&quot; you should be willing to sit there in-game for six, twelve, eighteen hours until the people ahead of you have gone. Better yet, just check every once in awhile when you have some time ahead of you, and if no one is there, plant your butt and wait for him to spawn. Sure, it's a rough road, but that's what happens when demand vastly exceeds supply.<br>
<br>
IF the Order of the Oaken is there 24/7 for many days, then that is rude. But not against the PnP policy. Sharing the spawn with you when you're not willing to sit there and wait for it is unreasonable. And it doesn't even sound like they monopolized the spawn that badly.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that's my opinion, for what it's worth. To answer your original question? Yes, I think you were a nice guy (not a sucker) for giving up the page to the people that were there ahead of you. For your actions afterwards... I think you have very unrealistic expectations. If you expect people to step aside for you without you sitting your butt down and waiting in-game for the spawn, you're setting yourself up for disappointment.<br>
<br>
My experience was: <br>
Stage I: get there and someone was ahead of me (no problem, I'll wait); wait a few hours; person ahead of my takes his spawn and leaves (congrats, adios, my turn)<br>
<br>
Stage II: wait another ~6 hours; someone showed up, sat around an hour, and then KSed my pop (after I had begun my attack, taken damage and dealt damage); leave for an hour to eat something and scream.<br>
<br>
Stage III: come back and a young hobbit is there ahead of me (sigh); I decide to wait again, cause she's obviously too young to take out Dylin; Dylin spawns and the young hobbit starts casting harmony on the smugglers; an ogre shaman runs outta nowhere, tries to kill Dylin, and dies; I asked the young hobbit if she was taking her turn now, but she decided she couldn't kill him, so I asked if I could take him and she said &quot;yes&quot;; so I killed Dylin and finally got my page. After approximately ~15 hours online with only one ~hour-long break.<br>
<br>
The camp is a pain, and anyone trying for it has my sympathy.<br>
<br>
