My typical approach on a camped item is to chat with the  campers on arrival.  So far, I've not run into anyone that thought they were &quot;camping&quot; something with an AFK mule -- lol, what a concept!  Why not treat this like Faydeydar?  You can put as many spotter mules as you want at the site, but it's the first one to start the attack that gets it.  Obviously, if someone real is there and ready, it's theirs.<br>
<br>
